messages.content: What does FeXCT be.cats stands for?
FeXCT be.cats is a custom node in ComfyUI that can be used to create or update the cats collection.
How do i use FeXCT be.cats?
First, run the FeXCT be.cats custom node in ComfyUI to create a cats collection or update an existing one. Additional details can be found in the GitHub link above.
What is the GitHub link provided?
The GitHub link provided is for the code repository of the FeXCT be.cats custom node for CoFyUI.
Can I install FeXCT be.cats through npm?
No, FeXCT be.cats is currently not available through npm. You can only install it using pip as described in the install instructions.
A custom node is a plugin or extension that can be added to ComfyUI to extend its functionality beyond its default capabilities.
What are the features of a custom node?
The features of a custom node can vary depending on the node itself, but can include things like image or video generation, data analysis, and more.
Can I modify the code for FeXCT be.cats?
Yes, the code for FeXCT be.cats is available on GitHub and can be modified as per your requirements. However, modifications should be done carefully to ensure backward compatibility.
